                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">White</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-12-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 19, 1902</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Hay acknowledges the receipt of Mr. White’s telegram mentioning the
                    President’s name as possible arbitrator, and states that <pb facs="0541" n="457"
                        xml:id="pg_457"/> while the President would not decline any service which
                    was desired by the powers interested for the settlement of pending claims he
                    would like Mr. White to intimate, discreetly and unofficially, to the British
                    minister for foreign affairs that he would regard it as altogether desirable
                    that the matter should be referred to The Hague.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
